     "Centralized and strong governments arise because of the
perception of unmet needs.  They maintain power because they
generate new perceptions of needs which are unmet or by
fueling the impressions which lead to war - or both.
     Take away the perception of unmet needs, and strong
governments find it increasingly difficult to maintain power
without becoming ever more tyrannical."





